# supabase/.env.example
#
# Local-dev values substituted into supabase/config.toml env() references (the CLI loads
# supabase/.env.local — gitignored — via dotenvx when running `supabase start` / `supabase
# status`). Copy to `supabase/.env.local` and fill in real local/dev values.
#
# These are AUTH-provider credentials read by GoTrue through config.toml substitution — they
# are NOT read by Edge Function code (those server-side vars live in supabase/functions/.env*).
# Same rule still applies (CLAUDE.md §3, docs/06 §9): server-side only, NEVER in apps/* or
# packages/*, never committed. Real values are local/dev only.

# --- Google OAuth (auth config, Phase 4.5) ---------------------------------
# Credentials for the Google sign-in provider configured in supabase/config.toml
# ([auth.external.google]). Create OAuth client credentials in a Google Cloud project.
SUPABASE_AUTH_EXTERNAL_GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID=replace-with-google-oauth-client-id
SUPABASE_AUTH_EXTERNAL_GOOGLE_SECRET=replace-with-google-oauth-client-secret
